In this article, President Joseph R. Biden Jr. reflects on the spirit of gratitude and unity that Thanksgiving represents in America. He highlights the historical origins of Thanksgiving, starting with the Pilgrims celebrating their successful harvest with the support of the Wampanoag people. He also mentions how George Washington and Abraham Lincoln recognized the importance of giving thanks in times of hardship. President Biden expresses his gratitude for the heroes in the country, including frontline workers, scientists, doctors, and veterans, who have contributed to the well-being of the nation. He emphasizes the significance of coming together as a nation and caring for one another. Lastly, President Biden proclaims Thursday, November 24, 2022, as a National Day of Thanksgiving and encourages the American people to reflect on the support they have received and express gratitude for their loved ones and communities.